{A day in the life of Jayne Thomas {continued.}
When I arrive home I go and change into my old clothes.I take my dog out and let him run after the rats that he can find,while I look at the calves. Then I go and see how the men are getting on with the silage.When I have done all that I go in for my tea.
For my tea I normally have a stew. After tea I go and feed the calves and help with the silage,I enjoy this alot.I have to move the straw to their shed to make the calves' beds.We are only on the first pile of silage ,we normally have about three.I go indoors when I get tired and watch television for a while and when I feel really tired I go to bed.This is a typical Thursday for me.
